## Primer Design & Phylogenetic Analysis of Codium sp. Using The *rbcL* Gene

Identifing the green algae *Codium spongiosum* by comparing the small nucleotide changes in the target gene of *rcbL*, a well presurved gene in the chloroplast that codes for the large subunit of the enzyme ribulose bisphosphate carboxylase/oxygenase (RuBisCO), to other species from the same genus.

Surching for "Codium rbcL" Nucleotides in NCBI resulting options for *Codium spongiosum* and several other species.

| Specie Name | *rcbL* gene code |
|---|---|
| *Codium spongiosum* | >KP686005.1 | 
| *Codium duthieae* | >KP686016.1 |
| *Codium lucasii* | >KP686023.1 |
| *Codium dwarkense* | >KP686019.1 |

Aligning the DNA coding sequences using ClustalW in MEGA softwere and locating target areas presence.

