[Primer3](https://primer3.ut.ee/) was used to run *rcbL* gene coding sequence of *Codium spongiosum* to generate the following Primers:  
| F/R | Sequence | Length | Tm | GC content | Amp. size | Position |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| F | GACGTCCACTTTTAGGTTGTACT | 23 | 58.37 | 43.48% | 205 bp | 3'th |
| R | TCACCAGTCTCAGCTTGTGA | 20 | 58.59 | 50% | 205 bp |  3'th |

[Primer-BLAST](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/tools/primer-blast/index.cgi) was used to verify the specifity of the generated primers.

![Codium Verify.jpg]({{site.baseurl}}/images/Codium%20Verify.jpg)  
*Out put while searched for specific primers on nucleotide data base od green algae*

Previous alignment was used to build a Neighbor-Joining phyligenetic tree in MEGA softwer. Tree was build under *Bootstrap* method with 1000 replications with *Kimura 2-parameter* model and *uniform rates* among sites. Missing or gaps in the data was dealth by *pairwize deletion*.

![Codium Tree.jpg]({{site.baseurl}}/images/Codium%20Tree.jpg)  
*Neighbor-Joining phylogenetic tree of aligned Codium sp. sequences*

In the phylogenetic tree there are four species of Codium clustered together.  
The two cloasest species shown in the image are *Codium lucasii* and *Codium spongiosum*, clustered together with their relatively short branch lengths (0.006 and 0.013 correspondly) suggest low genetic divergence. The two other cloasly related species clustered together are *Codium dwarkense* and *Codium duthieae* with a bit longer branch length between them (0.052 and 0.042 correspondly).  
Both groups have High bootstap sopport indicating that the main branches in the tree are highly reliable.